TOTAL Tanzania has lowered fuel price by 70/-in selected fuel stations for three days to celebrate Valentine day with its customers. The Network Operations Manager of Total fuel stations, Manager William Fillet said in a statement issued in Dar es Salaam yesterday that the price relief started on Wednesday (yesterday) until Friday (tomorrow). “The fuel price cut in some of the fuel stations is an expression of love to our customers as the country joins the rest in the world to celebrate Valentine day,” he said. Total Tanzania Head of Legal and Corporate Affairs Marsha Msuya said during the three day celebration also all women customers who will purchase any item in the Bonjour shops located in Total fuel stations will be given Valentine bouquet. A total of 16 Total fuel stations have been selected from the regions of Dar es Salaam, Dodoma, Arusha, Moshi in Kilimanjaro, Mwanza, Mbeya and Morogoro.